Changelog
8.4
  - fixed minimap exploration area being twice the size
  - fixed minor issue with internal GGPX downloader
  - fixed general minor errors
  - added an extra more transparent minimap option for GGPX loading

8.3
  - fixed minimap reveal reset on area change
  - fixed player stat readouts on specific events
  - fixed general minor errors

8.2
  - added POE 0.4.0 support
  - good luck everyone <3

8.1
- GGPX skill list loading feature
- general fixes and improvements

- POE2 :: GGPX UPDATE (temporarily)

- YOU MUST update all files - everything prior is outdated
  - use the '_GGPX download' button to get up to date files

8.0
- GGPX list loading feature
  - supports relative file paths
  - includes sample configurations
  - editable on-load via assistant or with notepad
  - keep a backup — updates overwrite the list file
  - significantly reduced ggpx load times

- refactored code for lower AV footprint and reduced intrusiveness

- YOU MUST update all files - everything prior is outdated
  - use the '_GGPX download' button to get up to date files

7.8
- general fixes and improvements

7.7
- fixed minimap reveal reset on re-entering a zone/map
  - works like before
  - no fuss / no caveat -> exactly as before

7.6
- updated offline game files for poe2
- added UI GGPX version display
- added UI download of current GGPX files
- added auto restart on certain UI options
  - keeping app elevation

7.5
- updated offline game files for 3.27
- added an UI option to reset game paths

7.4
- added support for upcoming 3.27 poe1 release
  - 99.99% sure we will have no delay at league start

- (experimental) reduced loading time with light/mid/heavy/blackscreen preset
  - non-essential stuff like sounds and effects are no longer being pre-loaded
  - report any issues or anomalies in #bug-report

- adjusted memory model to support dynamic runtime changes
- adjusted multi-threaded memory readouts
- updated internal patcher for compatibility with game "hotfix" updates
  - high probability for small hotfix updates being virtually irrelevant

- added "dual" autopot version for life and es to be considered at the same time
- added automatic detection for poe2 japanese game version
- added full support for japanese game version
- added client side system time synchronization even if disabled by windows settings

- added “low memory mode” for VM users
  - this will be active automatically while using blackscreen mode for botting
  - in theory it can safe up to 20% of system memory

- added minor internal metrics for future optimization
- improved accuracy of flask trigger logic under unstable frametime performance
- fixed high startup time on Hyper-V / VmWare
- fixed a rare lighting issue in interlude section of the game
- fixed a bug where bufflist occasionally duplicated expired entries
- fixed incorrect region parsing when game language is korean
- fixed a rare edge case of high cpu usage after conintious gameplay of 10+ hours
- fixed scaling issue at >200% dpi
- general cleanup of obsolete debug code

- improved support for handheld devices (others most likely work fine)
  - ASUS ROG Ally (X)
  - Lenovo Legion Go
  - MSI Claw (series)
  - AYANEO 2

7.3
- added japanese hideout detection

